Job Summary

Reporting to the Sr VP and Chief Information Officer, the role of the VP, Data & Analytics is critical to the success of Blue Shield of California (BSC) and the Information Technology organization in realizing its goals and objectives. This individual will play a critical role in leading and driving the data and analytics strategy to support progress towards achieving enterprise strategic priorities to enable next generation data architecture and analytics capability, supporting enterprise-wide application of analytics and data science to drive business value. S/he will work in close collaboration and partnership with all lines of business leaders, technology partners and enterprise functional leaders to establish and set priorities, identify opportunities, common themes and business needs, and develop enterprise-wide solutions and build new data and analytic capabilities evolving the transformation and innovation to a digitally driven healthcare system. As a member of IT Senior Leadership team, you will provide thought leadership and execution of strategies to integrate data and analytics from emerging trends such as digital, artificial intelligence, machine learning, social, third party and be the catalyst for identifying ongoing external trends and providing recommendations for the best optimization for the enterprise.

Responsibilities
Develop and establish a strategy and vision that shapes and drives data and analytics to enable the company to function more efficiently, identify growth opportunities, mitigate financial risk, and identify business cost savings opportunities, for all aspects of technology support;
Maintain an understanding of new and emerging technology trends and an awareness of innovative techniques and companies;
Proactively stay abreast of developments and trends to advance digital transformation efforts, understand the intersection of technology and business needs relevant to the enterprise to drive business innovation through data and analytics and bring those insights into actionable business value delivery outcomes;
Develop a deep understanding of the lines of business Portfolio and Products’ needs and priorities and work closely with each business to identify solutions that align with the enterprise strategy, leveraging enterprise solutions, and when needed specific solutions that are unique for that business;
Trusted advisor and consultant to business leaders across the enterprise; has strong ability to influence, thought partnership, and collaborate with executive leaders, technology leaders and partners, business stakeholders and their respective team;
Promote and lead a culture of operational excellence and continuous improvement for the daily support of data and analytics platform and constantly evolves and transforms based on the enterprise needs;
Develop, coach, and lead a high performing team, who manages a diverse team of professional that focuses on maximizing performance, business impact and results, as well as career development and succession plan;

Knowledge and Experience
Deep knowledge and experience in the data, analytics and business intelligence space including best in class solutions, strategy, tools, methodologies, data management, architecture, and business solutions;
Proven track record for working with and alongside technology leadership and business partners to improve, evolve and transform the strategy for data and analytics;
Proven ability to build the vision and strategy for leading an integrated technology data and analytics team;
Proven experience as a thought leader and innovator in the development of new tools, methodologies, and problem-solving approaches; including but not limited to experience in machine learning, artificial intelligence, cloud, and big data;
10+ years of advance analytics experience, with comprehensive knowledge of analytical tools and techniques utilized for statistical analysis, customer segmentation strategies, predictive modeling, behavioral analytics, program optimization, experimental test design, reporting and analysis design, and measurement strategy and development.
Deep experience in data architecture, data governance, warehousing, quality processes, and implementation. Skilled in structuring fact and dimension tables, leading logical and physical database design, data modeling, and reporting metadata and ETL processes.
8+ years of leading data and analytics across company or organization, technology a plus, and has successfully integrated and leveraged a strategic analytics function with business objectives, translating analytical model results into business insights and actionable customer management strategies, and yielding positive measurable financial outcomes.

Education/Credentials
The candidate will have a bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, MIS or related field. A master’s degree and/or equivalent experience with Information Systems is strongly preferred.

Key Job Competencies
Leadership
High IQ and EQ
Executive presence
Superior communication skills
Builds trust and relationships
Collaboration and Influencer
Drives results
Business acumen
Strategic Thinking
High integrity, ethics and clarity of purpose
